From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: georgewhewell <georgerw@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 18 May 2026 00:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] thunderbolt: xdomain: pin protocol handler owner while
 dispatching

XDomain protocol handlers are called from Thunderbolt control-ring work.
Out-of-tree service modules can unregister and unload while packets are
still being dispatched, because the protocol handler API does not hold a
module reference around the callback.

That leaves a race where tb_xdomain_handle_request() can call stale
module text or data after a reload/unload cycle. Add an optional owner
field to struct tb_protocol_handler and take a temporary module reference
while dispatching. In-flight handlers then make rmmod fail cleanly instead
of letting module memory disappear underneath the callback.

Signed-off-by: georgewhewell <georgerw@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/thunderbolt/xdomain.c | 6 ++++++
 include/linux/thunderbolt.h   | 5 +++++
 2 files changed, 11 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/thunderbolt/xdomain.c b/drivers/thunderbolt/xdomain.c
index d1d11f256ee1..d45f03207804 100644
--- a/drivers/thunderbolt/xdomain.c
+++ b/drivers/thunderbolt/xdomain.c
@@ -2627,6 +2627,9 @@ bool tb_xdomain_handle_request(struct tb *tb, enum tb_cfg_pkg_type type,
 			continue;
 
 		matched = true;
+		if (handler->owner && !try_module_get(handler->owner))
+			continue;
+
 		mutex_unlock(&xdomain_lock);
 		if (handler->callback_xd)
 			ret = handler->callback_xd(source_xd, buf, size,
@@ -2635,6 +2638,9 @@ bool tb_xdomain_handle_request(struct tb *tb, enum tb_cfg_pkg_type type,
 			ret = handler->callback(buf, size, handler->data);
 		mutex_lock(&xdomain_lock);
 
+		if (handler->owner)
+			module_put(handler->owner);
+
 		if (ret)
 			break;
 	}
diff --git a/include/linux/thunderbolt.h b/include/linux/thunderbolt.h
index f98f2c337918..46984409d5de 100644
--- a/include/linux/thunderbolt.h
+++ b/include/linux/thunderbolt.h
@@ -370,6 +370,8 @@ int tb_xdomain_request(struct tb_xdomain *xd, const void *request,
  *	      by this handler and should not be forwared to other
  *	      handlers.
  * @callback_xd: Like @callback, but also receives the source XDomain.
+ * @owner: Optional module that owns the callback. If set, XDomain core
+ *	   pins it while dispatching to avoid unload races.
  * @data: Data passed with the callback
  * @list: Handlers are linked using this
  *
@@ -382,11 +384,14 @@ int tb_xdomain_request(struct tb_xdomain *xd, const void *request,
  * directed to the service the driver implements.
  */
 #define TB_PROTOCOL_HANDLER_HAS_XDOMAIN 1
+#define TB_PROTOCOL_HANDLER_HAS_OWNER 1
+struct module;
 struct tb_protocol_handler {
 	const uuid_t *uuid;
 	int (*callback)(const void *buf, size_t size, void *data);
 	int (*callback_xd)(struct tb_xdomain *xd, const void *buf, size_t size,
 			   void *data);
+	struct module *owner;
 	void *data;
 	struct list_head list;
 };
-- 
